                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; names of the scribe and the donor; a
                           few lines on the incipit page of Texts I, II, IV, alternating with black
                           lines; incipit of Texts III, V, VI; incipit of the stanzas of Texts I,
                           III, V, VI and sections of Text II; abbreviations; elements of the
                           punctuation signs; elements of Ethiopic numerals.</seg>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <decoDesc>

                     <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d1">- <locus target="#1r">1r</locus> (incipit of
                        text I): simple coloured (black, red) ornamental band; geometric
                        motifs.</decoNote>
                     <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d2">- <locus target="#54r">54r</locus> (incipit
                        of text II): simple coloured ornamental band; geometric motifs.</decoNote>
                     <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d3">- <locus target="#90r">90r</locus> (incipit
                        of text IV): simple coloured (black, red) ornamental band; geometric
                        motifs.</decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="e1">
                           <desc type="findingAid">- Daily readings of Text I are indicated by the
                              names of the days of the week written in the upper margin, in thin
                              black frame: ዘሰሉስ: <locus target="#8r">fol. 8r</locus> ዘረቡዕ: <locus target="#15v">fol. 15v</locus> ዘሐሙስ: <locus target="#22v">fol.
                                 22v</locus> ዘአርብ: <locus target="#30v">fol. 30v</locus> ዘቀዳሚት:
                                 <locus target="#38r">fol. 38r</locus> ዘዕሁድ: <locus target="#45v">fol. 45v</locus>
                           </desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e3">
                           <desc>- Tämälläs-sign (in the shape of two perpendicular lines ┴) indicating the place where the omissions, written in the upper margin, belong: fols. 62r, 88v, 107v. - The ink from on <locus target="#74v">fol.  74v</locus> has imprinted on <locus target="#75r">fol.  75r</locus> and vice versa. - Remains of adhesive used to glue a mirror (now lost) are visible on the inner side of the front board.</desc>
                        </item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
